## Best Practices

### 1. Use Utility Classes

```tsx
// Good
<button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">
  Button
</button>

// Avoid
<button style=\{{ backgroundColor: 'blue', color: 'white', padding: '8px 16px' }}>
  Button
</button>
```

### 2. Extract Reusable Components

```tsx
// Good - Reusable component
export function Button({ children, variant = 'primary' }) {
  const baseClasses = 'px-4 py-2 rounded font-semibold transition-colors';
  const variantClasses = {
    primary: 'bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white',
    secondary: 'bg-gray-200 hover:bg-gray-300 text-gray-800',
  };

  return (
    <button className={`${baseClasses} ${variantClasses[variant]}`}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}

// Usage
<Button variant="primary">Primary</Button>
<Button variant="secondary">Secondary</Button>
```

### 3. Use Consistent Spacing

```tsx
// Good - Consistent spacing scale
<div className="space-y-4">  {/* 1rem / 16px */}
  <div className="p-4">Item 1</div>
  <div className="p-4">Item 2</div>
</div>

// Avoid - Arbitrary values
<div className="space-y-[13px]">
  <div className="p-[15px]">Item 1</div>
</div>
```

### 4. Mobile-First Design

```tsx
// Good - Mobile first
<div className="w-full md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3">
  Content
</div>

// Avoid - Desktop first
<div className="w-1/3 lg:w-1/2 md:w-full">
